Hero Group, the parent of  India â€™s
biggest motorcycle maker, plans to build 1,000 megawatts of
renewable energy capacity by 2017.  Its new unit, Hero Future Energies, completed its first
37.5-megawatt wind farm in Rajasthan state and has won a license
to build a 10-megawatt solar photovoltaic plant in Karnataka,
Hero Future Managing Director Rahul Munjal said in an e-mailed
statement today.  The company expects to develop 100 megawatts of wind and
solar projects this year, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
